s the rgb color to use as a low threshold color        - defaults to black (0,0,0)hi						- option arguments - 3 ints        - specifices the rgb color to use as a high threshold color        - defaults to white (255,255,255)varianta    - optional arguments - 1 int            - specifies the algorithm for constraining the colors												- 0 - pixel values are constrained to remain within the ranges given.  all operations done by the object are performed on a channel-by-channel basis, so the a pixel with a red value that exceeds the constraint will have its red value 'clipped' to the maximum range, regardless of whether the blue or green pixel values are within the ranges given.												- 1 - pixel values are forced out of the range, so that values within the ranges given are moved to the minimum or maximum value of the range, whichever is closest.												- 2 - pixel values outside of the range are forced to the rgb values specified by the lo and hi messages.  this is done on a channel-by-channel basis, so not all channels may be moved in any given pixel.												- 3 - pixel values inside of the range are forced to the rgb values specified by the lo or hi messages, whichever values are closer.